sentences: Ulrik Neumann (23 October 1918 – 28 June 1994) was a Danish film actor and musician.
He appeared in 19 films between 1940 and 1966.
From 1959 to 1961 he was a member of the trio Swe-Danes with the Swedish singer Alice Babs and the Danish jazz violinist Svend Asmussen.
He was born in Copenhagen, Denmark and died in Malmö, Sweden.
